    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-07-09T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-07-09T14:00:00-05:00" n="928"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d928">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">823.00 Revolutions/326: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Peru</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BWC1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Burdett</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-07-09T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >July 9, 1932—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 4:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>99. <persName corresp="#p_TMGRL1">Trujillo</persName> bombed from air yesterday
                    and prominent citizens telegraphed Government July 9, 1 p.m. offering surrender
                    of city to avoid further bombing. Troops after capturing Salaverry are advancing
                    on rebels from three sides and revolt should be promptly subdued if troops
                    continue loyal.</p>
                <p>The Embassy is attempting to communicate with <persName corresp="#p_WN1"
                        >Whyte</persName>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d928fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_WN1">Neil Whyte</persName>, Consular Agent at
                        Salaverry.</note> concerning safety of Americans. Nothing to indicate they
                    have been harmed. Panagra aviator reports that nothing abnormal in appearance at
                    Cartavio from the air. Press despatches from Lima are being strictly
                    censored.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BWC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Burdett</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
